Total Annual Compensation: $1.4M





Compensation as of Fiscal Year 2016. 

Glencore Plc Key Developments

Glencore plc Reports Production Results for the Second Quarter and Half Year of 2017; Provides Production Guidance for the Full Year of 2017
Jul 27 17
Glencore Plc reported production results for the second quarter and half year of 2017. For the period, the company reported own-sourced copper production of 642,900 tonnes was down 9%, reflecting a transition to mining a greater portion of copper/zinc ores at Antamina (noting concurrent higher zinc grades /production), temporary lower copper grades at Antapaccay, the effects of wet weather at Mutanda resulting in reduced ore throughput, and lower production /pit stability issues at Alumbrera as it nears end of life. Own-sourced zinc production of 570,800 tonnes was up 13%, reflecting the Antamina increase noted above and generally solid performances across the portfolio. Own-sourced nickel production of 51,200 tonnes was down 10%, reflecting scheduled maintenance at Murrin and INO, partly offset by the stabilising and improving performance at Koniambo. Attributable ferrochrome production of 836,000 tonnes was up 10%, reflecting more furnace production time, period over period, and strong furnace operational performances. Coal production of 61.1 million tonnes was up 4% on first half of 2016, mainly reflecting planned increases in the Australian coal portfolio.

For the quarter, the company reported production of copper of 318,800 tonnes against 368,000 tonnes a year ago. Zinc production was 291,600 tonnes against 249,400 tonnes a year ago. Gold production was 265,000 ounces against 257,000 ounces a year ago.

For the full year of 2017, the company expects copper production of 1,330,000 tonnes plus or minus 25, zinc production of 1,130,000 tonnes plus or minus 25, lead production of 285,000 tonnes plus or minus 10, nickel production of 115,000 tonnes plus or minus 4, ferrochrome production of 1,585 plus or minus 25 and coal production of 132 m tonnes plus or minus 3.


Glencore Bids For Rio Tinto
Jun 29 17
Bank of America Merrill Lynch has been engaged by Glencore Plc (LSE:GLEN) for a short advisory role on its bid to acquire Rio Tinto (ASX:RIO)'s Hunter Valley coal operations.


Glencore Makes Late Bid For Rio Tinto Coal Assets
Jun 23 17
Glencore Plc (LSE:GLEN) last-minute bid for Rio Tinto Limited (ASX:RIO)'s coking coal mines with a dilemma to mull over the weekend: accept less money or risk upsetting its biggest customer. On Friday afternoon in London, Glencore raised its bid for the mines, offering at least $225 million more than a proposal from Yanzhou Coal Mining Co, which Rio has already backed. 


